[anchor=findallocc][/anchor]
[b]Function:[/b] FindAllOcc();
[b]Syntax:[/b] FindAllOcc(LookFor, TheString : String) : Integer;
[b]What it does:[/b] Finds all the occurrences of what you're looking for in a string and returns how many times it was found.
[b]Note:[/b] This function requires the Replace() function before it.

FindAllOcc() function code only.
[code]
// The FindAllOcc() function finds all the occurrences of something in a string.
// Made by Ron. :)
Function FindAllOcc(LookFor, TheString : String) : Integer;
Var
  a : Integer;
  b : LongInt;
  FunctStr : String;
Begin
  FunctStr := TheString;
  Repeat
    b := Pos(LookFor, FunctStr);
    If(Not(b = 0))Then
    Begin
      a := a + 1;
    End;
    FunctStr := Replace(FunctStr, LookFor, '');
  Until(b = 0)
  Result := a;
End;
[/code]

Test the FindAllOcc() function by using this program.
[code]
