[anchor=shift][/anchor]
[b]Function:[/b] Shift();
[b]Syntax:[/b] Shift(TheString : String; HTML : Boolean) : String;
[b]What it does:[/b] It basically acts as a shift button and converts numbers, letters, and chars to its Shift form.
[b]Note:[/b] This function requires the Replace() function before it.

Shift() function code only: 
[code]
// The Shift() function will type in TheString as if shift was down.
// Made by Ron. :)
Function Shift(TheString : String; HTML : Boolean) : String;
Var
  i, c : Integer;
  Shifts, ShiftsA, Betw : String;
Begin
  Shifts  := '1234567890`-=[]\;''/,.';
  ShiftsA := '!@#$%^&*()~_+{}|:"?<>';
  For c := 1 to Length(TheString) do
  Begin
    For i := 1 to Length(Shifts) do
    Begin
      If(StrGet(TheString, c) = StrGet(Shifts, i))Then
      Begin
        TheString := Replace(TheString, StrGet(Shifts, i), StrGet(ShiftsA, i));
      End;
    End;
  End;
  TheString := Uppercase(TheString);
  If(HTML)Then
  Begin
    TheString := Replace(TheString, '<', '&lt;');
    TheString := Replace(TheString, '>', '&gt;');
  End;
  Result := TheString;
End;
[/code]

Test the Shift() function by using this program.
[code]
Program TestShiftFunction;

Var
  TheString : String;

